1-9811-76ea438c392c.webp?width=1000\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/profile-pics/4151e4bd-6243-4e85-a55d-285c3b22a74a_ccbb0885-0b9f-4a1e-ac33-adbabb4fa8c6.webp?width=1000\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/profile-pics/4151e4bd-6243-4e85-a55d-285c3b22a74a_764a1dba-b074-4ed2-8693-11957bebe965.webp?width=1000\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(250, 95, 119)\"><strong><em><mark style=\"background-color: rgb(249, 198, 199); color: inherit\">Additional Info:</mark></em></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(249, 198, 199)\">Is my bot speaking for you, speaking OOC or just being a silly goober in general? That is an LLM problem and no fault of my own. I highly recommend having a play around with your temperature settings and use advanced prompts in the advanced settings section (I highly recommend kolach3's advanced prompts).</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(249, 198, 199)\">I test my bots using the JLLM (I'm a broke bish so I can't afford any other API's), so if you use another API make sure to comment on the bot you are using and let me know how it's performing using other API!!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(249, 198, 199)\">I have silly Smooth brain moments here and there (spelling, putting the prompts in the wrong boxes when creating a bot, etc), but if I do so I will try to fix them as soon as possible. If I haven't already done so, please let me know in the ratings section below!!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/profile-pics/4151e4bd-6243-4e85-a55d-285c3b22